&lt;https://emsenn.net/library/domains/humanities/domains/sociology/domains/legalism/terms/tort/>
  rdf:type schema:Article ;
  schema:url &lt;https://emsenn.net/library/domains/humanities/domains/sociology/domains/legalism/terms/tort/> ;
  schema:name "tort" ;
  schema:description "A tort is a civil wrong — an act or omission that causes harm to another person and for which the law provides a remedy, typically monetary compensation. Tort law is distinct from criminal law: the state prosecutes crimes, but injured parties bring tort claims. The same act (an assault, for example) can be both a crime and a tort, prosecuted by the state and sued for by the victim." ;
